    instructions_worker_title: 'How This Works',
    instructions_worker_text: 'You are about to have a conversation with an AI assistant. It will listen to your situation and help you document what is happening.\n\nWhat the tool does:\n- Listens to your account of what is happening at your workplace\n- Helps place your situation within international labour standards that your employer is expected to respect\n- Creates a documented record that your trade union can use to take action\n\nWhat the tool does not do:\n- It cannot access external websites, databases, or legal libraries in real time\n- It does not have all the answers — it works with what you tell it\n- It is not a substitute for your trade union or legal advice\n\nDuring the conversation:\n- Describe your situation in your own words. There is no wrong way to start.\n- The assistant will ask you questions to understand what happened, when, where, and who was involved.\n- If you have documents, messages, or other evidence, you can upload them during the conversation using the upload button.\n- You can remain anonymous. You do not have to share your name or any personal details.\n\nWhen you are done:\n- Press the "End Session" button when you feel you have shared everything relevant.\n- The tool will generate a summary for you with the key points of your situation and how they relate to international standards.\n- A full report will be sent to UNI Global Union to support follow-up with your trade union.\n\nThe most important step you can take is to contact your local trade union. This tool supports that process — it does not replace it.',
    instructions_representative_title: 'How This Works',
    instructions_representative_text: 'You are about to have a conversation with an AI assistant. It will help you document a labour rights situation on behalf of the workers you represent.\n\nWhat the tool does:\n- Helps you build a structured case by gathering facts about what is happening, who is affected, and the scope of the situation\n- Identifies which international labour standards and employer commitments may be relevant\n- Creates a documented record that can be used for escalation through union channels\n\nWhat the tool does not do:\n- It cannot access external websites, databases, or legal libraries in real time\n- It does not have all the answers — it works with what you tell it\n- It is not a substitute for legal advice or formal complaint mechanisms\n\nDuring the conversation:\n- Describe the situation as clearly as you can: what is happening, how many workers are affected, and whether the issue is isolated or part of a pattern.\n- The assistant will ask follow-up questions to fill in details that strengthen the case — dates, locations, evidence, and the company\'s own commitments or policies.\n- If you have documents, statements, or other evidence, you can upload them during the conversation using the upload button.\n- Worker identities are kept anonymous in all reports shared outside UNI Global Union.\n\nWhen you are done:\n- Press the "End Session" button when you feel you have shared everything relevant.\n- The tool will generate a case summary identifying the key facts, relevant international frameworks, and points for escalation.\n- A full report will be sent to UNI Global Union for evaluation and follow-up with your national union.\n\nShare this report with your national union. It is the starting point for coordinated action — this tool documents, but does not submit complaints on your behalf.',
    instructions_organizer_title: 'How to Use HRDD Helper',
    instructions_organizer_text: 'HRDD Helper is an AI assistant that helps you work with international labour standards in the context of workers\' rights cases.\n\nBefore you start, you will select a consultation mode that determines how the tool interacts with you. Choose the mode that matches what you need right now.\n\nDuring the conversation:\n- The assistant responds in the language you selected. You can also write in that language throughout.\n- Ask questions, describe situations, or submit materials — the assistant adapts to the mode you have chosen.\n- You can upload documents (evidence, statements, reports) at any time using the upload button. The assistant will analyse their content within the conversation.\n- The AI works with its built-in knowledge of ILO Conventions, OECD Guidelines, UN Guiding Principles, EU CSDDD, and FSC Standards. It does not access external websites or databases in real time.\n\nWhen you are done:\n- Press "End Session" to close the conversation.\n- The tool generates a structured summary based on your session.\n- For documentation and submission modes, a full case report is also generated for UNI Global Union internal use.',
    instructions_officer_title: 'How to Use HRDD Helper',
    instructions_officer_text: 'HRDD Helper is an AI assistant that helps you work with international labour standards in the context of workers\' rights cases.\n\nBefore you start, you will select a consultation mode that determines how the tool interacts with you. Choose the mode that matches what you need right now.\n\nDuring the conversation:\n- The assistant responds in the language you selected. You can also write in that language throughout.\n- Ask questions, describe situations, or submit materials — the assistant adapts to the mode you have chosen.\n- You can upload documents (evidence, statements, reports) at any time using the upload button. The assistant will analyse their content within the conversation.\n- The AI works with its built-in knowledge of ILO Conventions, OECD Guidelines, UN Guiding Principles, EU CSDDD, and FSC Standards. It does not access external websites or databases in real time.\n\nYou have access to all consultation modes, including Training. In Training mode, no case is documented — the tool acts as a teaching resource on international frameworks. Use it for your own learning or to prepare training materials for your affiliates.\n\nWhen you are done:\n- Press "End Session" to close the conversation.\n- The tool generates a structured summary based on your session.\n- For documentation and submission modes, a full case report is also generated for UNI Global Union internal use.',
